text: Caddo is one of the sixty-four parishes in the U.S. state of Louisiana. The parish seat and most populous municipality is Shreveport. As of the 2020 count, 237,848 people lived there. It is the largest parish in the North Louisiana region and the fourth-largest in the state. ==References== Category:1838 establishments in the United States Category:1830s establishments in Louisiana
title: Caddo Parish, Louisiana
